üíæ Azure Fundamentals ‚Äì Describe Azure Storage Services
Module Completed: Describe Azure storage services
Status: ‚úÖ Module assessment passed
Achievement: Badge earned

üìò Concepts Covered
üì¶ Azure Storage Types
Blob Storage
Stores unstructured data like images, videos, documents, backups.
Optimized for large amounts of data.
Tiers: Hot, Cool, Archive.

Disk Storage
Used with Azure VMs for OS and data disks.
High-performance SSD and HDD options.

File Storage
Fully managed file shares using SMB protocol.
Supports lift-and-shift scenarios, and on-prem integration.

Queue Storage
Messaging store for reliable asynchronous communication between components.

Table Storage
NoSQL key-value store for structured data.
Good for large-scale data with fast access needs.

üîê Storage Access & Security
Shared Access Signature (SAS):
Provides delegated, time-limited access to storage resources.

Storage Account Keys:
Primary and secondary keys provide full access ‚Äî should be rotated regularly.

Azure AD Integration:
Modern, role-based access via Azure Active Directory.

üîÑ Redundancy & Replication Options
LRS (Locally Redundant Storage)
Replicates data within a single datacenter.

GRS (Geo-Redundant Storage)
Replicates across regions for disaster recovery.

ZRS (Zone-Redundant Storage)
Replicates across availability zones in one region.

üß† Summary Table
Storage Type	Purpose	Use Case
Blob Storage	Unstructured data	Images, videos, backups
File Storage	SMB-compatible file shares	Lift-and-shift apps, shared files
Queue Storage	Async messaging	Decoupled systems, event-driven
Table Storage	NoSQL structured data	Key-value lookups, large datasets
Disk Storage	VM disks	OS, temp, and data disks
